abstract: The former president and his allies have given often conflicting defenses of his retention of classified documents, without addressing why he had kept them.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON  First he said that he was working and cooperating with government agents who he claimed had inappropriately entered his home. Then, when the government revealed that the F.B.I., during its search, had recovered nearly a dozen sets of documents that were marked classified, he suggested the agents had planted evidence.

main: Trumps Shifting Explanations Follow a Familiar Playbook
print_headline: Trump Using Familiar Defensive Tactic to Explain F.B.I. Search

abstract: A new book by Scott J. Shapiro, a law and philosophy professor at Yale, examines breaches of cybersecurity and their implications for keeping information safe.
snippet: A new book by Scott J. Shapiro, a law and philosophy professor at Yale, examines breaches of cybersecurity and their implications for keeping information safe.
lead_paragraph: Dont let the adorable title fool you: As Scott J. Shapiro acknowledges in Fancy Bear Goes Phishing, his new book about cybersecurity, hacking can inflict terrible harm. Shapiro is the author, with Oona A. Hathaway, of The Internationalists (2017), which recounts 20th-century efforts to outlaw war; among the numerous questions animating Fancy Bear Goes Phishing is whether hacking has opened the door to war by other means.

main: In Fancy Bear Goes Phishing, Tales of Harmful Hacks

value: Fancy Bear Goes Phishing: The Dark History of the Information Age, in Five Extraordinary Hacks (Book)

abstract: The producer and pop singer, long a proponent of technological experimentation, has open-sourced her voice using new A.I. tools. Shes been impressed by the results.
snippet: The producer and pop singer, long a proponent of technological experimentation, has open-sourced her voice using new A.I. tools. Shes been impressed by the results.
lead_paragraph: Last month, when Heart on My Sleeve, a track credited to A.I. versions of Drake and the Weeknd, became an unauthorized hit online, many in the music industry loudly fretted about the legal and creative risks to come. But Grimes, the producer and pop singer who has long been enthralled with visions of the future, saw opportunity.

main: Grimes Invited Anyone to Make A.I. Grimes Songs. Here Are Her Reviews.

abstract: For 25 years he was editor of The Concord Monitor, an award-winning go-to source every four years for national reporters covering the New Hampshire presidential primary.
snippet: For 25 years he was editor of The Concord Monitor, an award-winning go-to source every four years for national reporters covering the New Hampshire presidential primary.
lead_paragraph: Mike Pride, who transformed the New Hampshire newspaper The Concord Monitor into a prizewinning paragon of regional journalism, mentoring generations of reporters and editors, defying the trope about the dying small-town newspaper and exerting an outsize impact on his profession, died on April 24 in a hospice in Palm Harbor, Fla. He was 76.

main: Mike Pride, Who Proved a Regional Newspaper Could Work, Dies at 76
print_headline: Mike Pride, 76, New Hampshire Editor  Who Transformed a Newspaper, Dies

abstract: In Paris, a moving and wistful performance installation by Lina Lapelyte gathers untrained singers for reflections on regret and inability.
snippet: In Paris, a moving and wistful performance installation by Lina Lapelyte gathers untrained singers for reflections on regret and inability.
lead_paragraph: PARIS  The first time I sang, it was by ear. I imagine thats often the case. Toddlers join their favorite characters in Disney movies or echo their parents with mumbled renditions of Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star. When children begin to sing in school, they usually learn not from scores, but from lyrics memorized through repetition.

main: Review: The Mutes Gives Voice to Musical Outsiders
print_headline: Straining for Harmony Through Clouds of Regret
